{"section": "Exercise 3.21.3: Solving linear homogeneous recurrence relations.", "qid": 4, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n Match each characteristic equation for a recurrence relation\nto the expression denoting the solutions to the recurrence relation.\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   3)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   Suppose that another one of the initial values for the previous question is g\n   <sub>\n    1\n   </sub>\n   = 3. Which one of the linear equations holds for variables s and t?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <fieldset>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember157\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"3s - 2t = 3.\" name=\"43\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember156&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    3s - 2t = 3.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember159\">\n   <input aria-label=\"3s - 2t = 1.\" name=\"43\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember158&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    3s - 2t = 1.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember161\">\n   <input aria-label=\"-3s + 2t = 3.\" name=\"43\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember160&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    -3s + 2t = 3.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n </fieldset>\n</div>\n", "choices": [], "answer": "<div class=\"answer\">\n <p>\n  Characteristic equation: x\n  <sup>\n   3\n  </sup>\n  - 3x\n  <sup>\n   2\n  </sup>\n  - 4x + 12 = (x + 2)(x - 2)(x - 3).\n </p>\n <p>\n  Roots of the characteristic equation: -2, 2, 3.\n </p>\n <p>\n  General solution: b\n  <sub>\n   n\n  </sub>\n  = a\n  <sub>\n   0\n  </sub>\n  (-2)\n  <sup>\n   n\n  </sup>\n  + a\n  <sub>\n   1\n  </sub>\n  2\n  <sup>\n   n\n  </sup>\n  + a\n  <sub>\n   2\n  </sub>\n  3\n  <sup>\n   n\n  </sup>\n </p>\n <p>\n  Plug in initial values for n = 0, n = 1, and n = 2:\n </p>\n <ul>\n  <li>\n   b\n   <sub>\n    0\n   </sub>\n   = 4 =  a\n   <sub>\n    0\n   </sub>\n   (-2)\n   <sup>\n    0\n   </sup>\n   + a\n   <sub>\n    1\n   </sub>\n   2\n   <sup>\n    0\n   </sup>\n   + a\n   <sub>\n    2\n   </sub>\n   3\n   <sup>\n    0\n   </sup>\n   = a\n   <sub>\n    0\n   </sub>\n   + a\n   <sub>\n    1\n   </sub>\n   + a\n   <sub>\n    2\n   </sub>\n   .\n  </li>\n  <li>\n   b\n   <sub>\n    1\n   </sub>\n   = -5  =  a\n   <sub>\n    0\n   </sub>\n   (-2)\n   <sup>\n    1\n   </sup>\n   + a\n   <sub>\n    1\n   </sub>\n   2\n   <sup>\n    1\n   </sup>\n   + a\n   <sub>\n    2\n   </sub>\n   3\n   <sup>\n    1\n   </sup>\n   = -2a\n   <sub>\n    0\n   </sub>\n   + 2a\n   <sub>\n    1\n   </sub>\n   + 3a\n   <sub>\n    2\n   </sub>\n   .\n  </li>\n  <li>\n   b\n   <sub>\n    2\n   </sub>\n   = 11  =  a\n   <sub>\n    0\n   </sub>\n   (-2)\n   <sup>\n    2\n   </sup>\n   + a\n   <sub>\n    1\n   </sub>\n   2\n   <sup>\n    2\n   </sup>\n   + a\n   <sub>\n    2\n   </sub>\n   3\n   <sup>\n    2\n   </sup>\n   = 4a\n   <sub>\n    0\n   </sub>\n   + 4a\n   <sub>\n    1\n   </sub>\n   + 9a\n   <sub>\n    2\n   </sub>\n   .\n  </li>\n </ul>\n <p>\n  Solve a\n  <sub>\n   0\n  </sub>\n  + a\n  <sub>\n   1\n  </sub>\n  + a\n  <sub>\n   2\n  </sub>\n  = 4 and -2a\n  <sub>\n   0\n  </sub>\n  + 2a\n  <sub>\n   1\n  </sub>\n  + 3a\n  <sub>\n   2\n  </sub>\n  = -5 and 4a\n  <sub>\n   0\n  </sub>\n  + 4a\n  <sub>\n   1\n  </sub>\n  + 9a\n  <sub>\n   2\n  </sub>\n  = 11.\n </p>\n <p>\n  a\n  <sub>\n   0\n  </sub>\n  = 3, a\n  <sub>\n   1\n  </sub>\n  = 2, and a\n  <sub>\n   2\n  </sub>\n  = -1.\n </p>\n <p>\n  Solution: b\n  <sub>\n   n\n  </sub>\n  = 3(-2)\n  <sup>\n   n\n  </sup>\n  + 2\u00b72\n  <sup>\n   n\n  </sup>\n  -3\n  <sup>\n   n\n  </sup>\n  = 3(-2)\n  <sup>\n   n\n  </sup>\n  +2\n  <sup>\n   n+1\n  </sup>\n  - 3\n  <sup>\n   n\n  </sup>\n </p>\n</div>\n", "explanation": null}